## Phase Contracts

Each phase must finish with a concrete state update before the next phase starts.

- PLAN creates or updates the design document and decides task complexity.
- ARCHITECTURE runs only for RED work or when a configured rule requires it.
- IMPLEMENTATION changes code inside the approved scope and records verification.
- SIMPLIFY is behavior-preserving and happens before REVIEW.
- REVIEW triages findings before FIX work starts.
- FIX addresses accepted findings and records targeted verification.
- QUALITY_GATE runs configured experts plus pack-contributed validators.
- QA validates the user-facing or runtime surface touched by the task.
- DELIVERY records final evidence, documentation changes, and delivery state.

Before a phase transition, validate the current phase report and state fields.

